				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
								<div class="elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix">
				<p>International markets offer plenty of opportunity for chains to expand and claim market share, whether they be Western brands looking to create (or grow) a global footprint to complement their domestic presence or systems from other regions hoping to claim more food spend both domestically and abroad.</p><p>The above strategy for going into new markets as an operator is an exceptional strategy for growing a global brand on an accelerated path.</p><p>As global foodservice advisors, we’ve seen a lot of international restaurant expansion via cross-border M&amp;A activity over the last decade (and many deals that are off the market). The bigger the deal the easiest it is to find investors interested. Having a partner to identify targets, make the connection, initiate discussions, and get things through is key to avoid over-burdening the current systems.</p>					</div>
